-- Ukraine May Abolish VAT on Imported Oil, Kommersant Reports
-- B y   D a r y n a   K r a s n o l u t s k a
-- 2012-06-20T07:40:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-20/ukraine-may-abolish-vat-on-imported-oil-kommersant-reports.html
Ukraine’s government is considering
abolishing a value-added tax on imported crude oil to stabilize
the market,  Kommersant-Ukraine  newspaper reported, citing a
person with knowledge of the matter from the Energy and Coal
Industry Ministry.  The tax may be scrapped for 10 million metric tons of oil a
year that’s being processed at Ukrainian refineries, the
newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Daryna Krasnolutska in Kiev at 
